My research focuses on broad visual perception and on models that can generalize to perform multiple
tasks. I work on understanding and leveraging how visual problems are related to each other. My advisor
is Dr. Silvio Savarese, and I am also supervised by Dr. Amir Zamir.
I worked on parallelizing computing within PowerPoint Designer. Designer is a service which uses both
expert systems and modern machine learning to lay out content on slides. As a side contribution, I
developed a CNN-based system to identify logos on slides.
